    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>How Black Comedy Got the Last Laugh</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Mark Elliott letter opposes Lynn Hirschberg's September 3 article for focusing on comedian Chris Tucker's race; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I enjoyed Lynn Hirschberg's profile of Chris Tucker. Here's a guy who tries to define himself without referring to his skin color, but your writer wouldn't let him. Had Jim Carrey or Greg Kinnear decided to take the same career track (no agent, picky about parts), he would be described as daring and revolutionary, not ''nave and lucky.''</p>
        <p>Mark Elliott  Harbor Springs, Mich.</p>
      </block>
